INSTRUCTIONS 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
can be edited under section Editable Instructions

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
EDITABLE CODE 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
check below for (relatively) easily editable parameters, stimuli, instructions etc. 
Keep in mind that you can use this script as a template and therefore always "mess" with the entire code 
to further customize your experiment.

The parameters you can change are:

/line_fontheight:				sets the height of the lines in % screen height (default: 20%)

/responsekeyleft:				the left response key (default: "A")
/responsekeyright:       		 the right response key (default: "L")

/color1:						sets the first target color (here: red)
/color2:						sets the second target color (here: blue)
/alternativecolor1:				sets the first alternative color (here: yellow)

/alternativecolor2:				sets the second alternative color (here: purple), used in control
								condition when color is held constant and only tilt is changing

/responsetimeout:				sets how much time participants have to respond in ms (here: 5000ms)

/regularresttime:				rest time after each block in ms (default: 30000ms )
/prolongedresttime:				rest time during specified long rest blocks in ms (default: 150000 => 2.5 minutes)
/prolongedrest:					determines after how many blocks a prolonged rest block should be given (default:10)


/nrTrialsPerPracticeblock:		the number of trials per practice block that should be run (default: 24)
									Note: 48 is the maximum that will run
									
/nrTrialsPerTestblock:			the number of trials per test block that should be run (default: 24)
									Note: 48 is the maximum that will run

</usermanual>


**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE PARAMETERS: change editable parameters here
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************

<parameters>
/ line_fontheight = 20%

/ responsekeyleft = "A"
/ responsekeyright = "L"

/ color1 = red
/ color2 = blue
/ alternativecolor1 = yellow
/ alternativecolor2 = purple

/responsetimeout = 2000

/regularresttime = 30000
/prolongedresttime = 150000
/ prolongedrest = 10

/nrTrialsPerPracticeblock = 24
/nrTrialsPerTestblock = 24
</parameters>

**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE STIMULI: change editable stimuli here
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************

Note: Stimuli presented inside the box
<item lines>
/ 1 = "/"
/ 2 = "\"
/ 3 = "│"
</item>

Alternative Set of Stimuli where compatibility issues between location of keys on the keyboard
(left vs. right) and tilt (left vs right) might be avoided:

/1 = "˄"
/2 = "˅"
/3 = "◊"


<item restinstructions>
/ 1 = "Take a break"
</item>

<item feedback>
/ 1 = "ERROR"
</item>

**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE INSTRUCTIONS: change instructions here
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************

<instruct>
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 2.5%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
</instruct>


<item instructions>
/1 = "Welcome!

This is a study about Attention. In this task you will see a box, such as this, in the middle of the screen. Inside the box there is a line.
~n~n~n~n~n~n~n~n~n
The box and the line can change COLOR; the line can change TILT (where it's pointing)."
/2 = "There are going to be two main tasks: 
Pay attention to the color OR pay attention to the tilt.
~n~n~n~n~n~n~n~n~n~n"
/3 = "TILT TASK:

If you are asked to pay attention to the tilt of the line, you will notice that the line can either be tilted to the RIGHT or the LEFT.
~n~n~n~n~n~n~n~n~n~n
When you are asked to pay attention to the TILT of the line, try to IGNORE the COLOR of the line and the COLOR of the box.

Press '<%values.tilt1key%>' if the line tilts to the RIGHT.
Press '<%values.tilt2key%>' if the line tilts to the LEFT."
/4 = "COLOR TASK:

If you are asked to pay attention to COLOR, you might be asked to pay attention to the color of the line or the color of the box.
~n~n~n~n~n~n~n~n~n~n
When you are asked to pay attention to the color, try to ignore the tilt of the line.

Press '<%values.color1key%>' if the COLOR is RED.
Press '<%values.color2key%>' if the COLOR is BLUE."
/5 = "Practice

We will now practice the task.
There will be four blocks of practice. Before each block starts, you will be told whether you should pay attention to the COLOR or the TILT of the line.

You will also be reminded of the response keys.

Press Spacebar to start practice."
/6 = "This is the end of practice.
Press Spacebar to start the actual test."
</item>

<text continue>
/ items = ("Spacebar >>")
/ fontstyle = ("Courier New", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ vjustify = center
/ size = (30%, 5%)
/ txcolor = white
/ txbgcolor = lightGray
/ position = (85%, 95%)
</text>

<text goback>
/ items = ("<< B")
/ fontstyle = ("Courier New", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ vjustify = center
/ size = (30%, 5%)
/ txcolor = white
/ txbgcolor = lightGray
/ position = (15%, 95%)
</text>

<text start>
/ items = ("Spacebar to START")
/ fontstyle = ("Courier New", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ vjustify = center
/ size = (30%, 5%)
/ txcolor = white
/ txbgcolor = green
/ position = (85%, 95%)
</text>

<text attention_color_line>
